  Another of the popular items shared was a salad made by Jessica Marshall.  Below is the recipe she used to prepare this delicious dish.

Salad:
1 bag of baby spinach
1 bag of other lettuce mix (romaine, iceberg, etc)
Candied nuts to taste – maybe ½ cup or so
Dried cranberries to taste – maybe ½ cup or so
2-3 chopped shallots
Cheese – goat/feta/parmesan to taste – maybe ½-1 cup
1 apple sliced (fuji/granny smith/etc)

Dressing – adjust amounts to taste:
1/3 c olive oil
1/3 c apple cider vinegar
2-3 tbs good quality raspberry jam
Good pinch of salt
Good pinch of pepper
1 tbs chopped shallot
*Let it sit overnight.
